description.narrative:
Civic organization Agency for Legislative Initiatives has applied to Sida for funding of 14 989 374 SEK to help implement its organizational strategy which contributes to development and promotion of the civic, political and economic concepts of the democratic state that is based on the rule of law. Its programmatic activities are underpinned by its mission envisaging the establishment of democratic values in the Ukrainian society, facilitate the development of effective and well-balanced public policies in Ukraine and to develop political and legal culture of citizens, particularly that of politicians.

Consequently, ALI pursues its strategic objectives by working in four key directions:
Good Governance that consists of working to reform of the Ukrainian Parliament, reforming public governance, and support of the implementation of the Association Agreement with the European Union and a few other sectoral reforms in the Ukrainian public sector;

• Justice and Security; the advocacy to reform of the Prosecutor General’s Office and the Ministry of Internal Affairs, promoting judiciary reform as well as facilitation of the development of education standards in law degrees and other specializations;

• Civic and Political Culture that is implemented through the Ukraine School of Political Studies (USPS) and the projects on social audits of the municipalities, as well as promoting innovative approaches and practices in social and political spheres;

• Organizational Development of ALI itself that consists of boosting the communication capacities, improving internal policies and procedures and human capital development, as well as the other organizational development efforts. 

The latter is in line with a second objective which aims to facilitate the transition of the Agency for Legislative Initiatives (ALI), an organization with 20 years of experience, to a qualitatively higher level of independence, sustainability, transparency and resilience in accordance with the best global standards for non-governmental organizations and think tanks.
